- 'Highly Active' is defined as users who burn more than 3000 calories and have a BMI greater than 25;
- 'Moderately Active' is defined as users who burn between 2000 and 3000 calories and have a BMI between 18.5 and 25;
- 'Sedentary' is defined as users who burn fewer than 2000 calories and have a BMI less than 18.5;
- 'Lightly Active' is a catch-all category for users who do not fall into the above categories;
- 'Good' sleep quality is defined as users who sleep between 7 and 9 hours;
- 'Excellent' sleep quality is defined as users who sleep 9 hours or more;
- 'Poor' sleep quality is defined as users who sleep fewer than 7 hours;
- 'Fair' sleep quality is a catch-all category for users who do not fall into the above categories.

